4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ADDING TO THE DUTIES OF THE TRANSPORTATION INTERIM
5 COMMITTEE, THE TRANSPORTATION COMMISSION, AND THE DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION
6 REGARDING CONSTRUCTION PROJECT PRIORITIZATION; REQUIRING THE TRANSPORTATION
7 INTERIM COMMITTEE TO PREPARE FOR PREINTRODUCTION A JOINT RESOLUTION RECOMMENDING
8 THAT THE COMMISSION PRIORITIZE CERTAIN CONSTRUCTION AND RECONSTRUCTION PROJECTS;
9 REQUIRING THE COMMISSION TO REPORT BIENNIALLY TO THE TRANSPORTATION INTERIM
10 COMMITTEE ON THE STATUS OF PROJECTS RECOMMENDED BY THE LEGISLATURE; REQUIRING
11 THE DEPARTMENT TO ASSIST THE COMMISSION IN CONSIDERING PROJECTS RECOMMENDED BY
12 THE LEGISLATURE; ESTABLISHING REPORTING REQUIREMENTS; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 5-5-233
13 AND 60-2-110, MCA.”
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
16
17 Section 1. Section 5-5-233, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "5-5-233. Transportation interim committee. (1) The transportation interim committee has
19 administrative rule review, draft legislation review, program evaluation, and monitoring functions for the
20 department of transportation, the motor vehicle division of the department of justice, and the entities attached to
21 the department of transportation for administrative purposes.
22 (2) (a) The committee shall prepare for preintroduction into each regular session of the legislature
23 a joint resolution of the legislature recommending to the transportation commission construction and
24 reconstruction projects for prioritization pursuant to 60-2-110.
25 (b) The committee may prepare for preintroduction additional legislation to facilitate the prioritizing
26 of projects previously recommended by the legislature but not subsequently prioritized by the transportation
27 commission."
