1 Section 2. Section 60-2-110, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "60-2-110. Setting priorities and selecting projects -- reporting. (1) Except as provided in 60-2-
3 133, the commission shall establish priorities and select and designate segments for construction and
4 reconstruction on the national highway system, the primary highway system, the secondary highway system,
5 the urban highway system, and state highways.
6 (2) The commission shall consult with the board of county commissioners of the county in which a
7 highway is located when establishing priorities and when selecting and designating segments on the secondary
8 highway system for construction and reconstruction.
9 (3) The commission shall consult with the appropriate local government authorities when
10 establishing priorities and selecting and designating segments on the urban highway system for construction
11 and reconstruction.
12 (4) (a) The commission shall report biennially to the transportation interim committee in
13 accordance with 5-11-210 on the status of construction and reconstruction projects recommended for
14 prioritization by joint resolution of the legislature. The report must be delivered in May of even-numbered years,
15 unless a different time is agreed to by the committee and the commission.
16 (b) If a project recommended by the legislature has not been prioritized, the commission shall
17 include in its report the technical, financial, and other factors that influenced its decision.
18 (4)(5) The commission shall use information gathered or discovered by and documents prepared by
19 the department, and department officials and employees shall provide assistance and advice, including the
20 preparation of documents necessary to help the commission to consider projects recommended by the
21 legislature.
22 (5)(6) The commission shall establish and determine priorities and projects for rail and transit
23 programs and, to the extent possible, coordinate intermodal transportation within the state.
24 (6)(7) In carrying out the requirements of this section, the department shall:
25 (a) make recommendations to the commission;
26 (b) establish the requirements and procedures for administering this section; and
27 (c) take all reasonable steps to ensure the integrity and viability of agricultural and rural
28 transportation and related needs."
